 "executive_summary": "This work presents the first crystal structure of a human TCR bound to a viral peptide presented on HLA-A2, establishing the molecular architecture of MHC-I recognition. The TCR engages the peptide\u2013MHC complex through its variable loops, which contact nearly the entire peptide surface while also engaging a substantial area of the MHC molecule itself, and adopts a diagonal orientation across the peptide-binding groove that appears conserved across both class I and class II MHC molecules. This general binding geometry has profound implications for understanding how the immune repertoire is selected during development and explains the structural basis for alloreactivity\u2014the ability of TCRs to cross-react with peptides presented on different MHC alleles.",
